prompt:

YOU MUST WRITE EXACTLY 1000-1200 CHARACTERS. COUNT EVERY SINGLE CHARACTER.

WRITE EXACTLY THREE PARAGRAPHS. STOP WHEN YOU REACH 1200 CHARACTERS.

TARGET LENGTH: 1100 CHARACTERS

END WITH A COMPLETE SENTENCE AND A PERIOD (.)

DO NOT STOP WRITING UNTIL YOU REACH AT LEAST 1000 CHARACTERS. THIS IS MANDATORY.

Your response must be substantive and detailed. DO NOT write short summaries.

In the 1980s, the Internet Protocol (IP) was developed, allowing different networks to communicate with each other.  The World Wide Web (WWW) was invented in 1989 by Tim Berners-Lee, making it easy for people to access and share information using web browsers and hyperlinks. The internet expanded rapidly in the 1990s, with the widespread adoption of dial-up internet and the emergence of online services like America Online (AOL) and CompuServe.  By 2030, the internet will be even more integrated into daily life, with the Internet of Things (IoT) connecting billions of devices and enabling new applications like smart homes and cities, and the internet will continue to revolutionize the way we live and work, with artificial intelligence and machine learning playing a major role in shaping its future, and it will be more secure and accessible to everyone.
